vectorData.altText: That's right!  This is the costal, or subcostal groove. It is a landmark for the intercostal nerve, artery and vein.

The costal groove runs along the inferior border of the rib on its internal surface. With that, you now know “up from down” and can correctly orient the rib in your hand.

It is at these facets that ribs articulate with the vertebral column.
Now that you know “up from down” and which end articulates with the vertebral column, you can determine whether the rib in your hand is from the right or left side of the body.
